Command Line Arguments
make
java ExamTester

In the following program, a file with the name 'exam.txt' is loaded and then user 
is asked to enter their name. After that the contents of the 'exam.txt' file are 
outputted into the console. The user is then one by one asked to answer the questions 
contained in the file ranging from short answer, multiple choice, multiple choice multiple 
answers. A dafualt 'exam.txt' file is provided. After user finishes the exam, score 
for each question and total score is displayed. Lastly, it then creates two .txt files called 
'answers.txt' which stores the user's answers and 'shuffled.txt' which has the questions 
from the exam.txt file shuffled. 